  body

    include header
    
    .container-fluid.padded

        h3 Note
        p youtube.tracking.exposed (ytTREX) is free software project designed to help study, uncover and then visualize the reccomentation algorithms in YouTube.
        p It is a prototype, part of a greater 
            a(href="https://tracking.exposed") project
            |  on algorithmic bias and filter bubbles in social networks, Google, and other products large tech companies make.

        p.yt-red-b.white.centered
            span This is a NON WORKING ALPHA VERSION, don't use it! it is online only for concept feedback and developers.
    
        h3 This project been announced at 35c3 as part of the panel: 
            a(href="https://fahrplan.events.ccc.de/congress/2018/Fahrplan/events/9797.html") Analyzing the Facebook algorithm and reclaim algorithm sovreignty
            |. The goal of this non working release is to attract interested hackers, data analysts, or human scientists interested in research on the impact of personalization algorithms in youtube.

